descriptionHtml:
Cities RnE-Winterhold
Download - http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/40127
Reduced n Enhanced (RnE) packages by Thorne67
Made for FPS Boosts on low end machines
FINAL VERSION. In conjunction with my Farmhouses. They are both FINAL.
NEXUS EXCLUSIVE.
NON MESHED VERSION. NO REQUIREMENTS. HAS ESPs. READ BELOW.

Ok. First of all. Running low rez textures on low 
settings just WONT work well.  The best way to 
use THESE is to download a Low rez pack such as 
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/47 
or 
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/14504 
and overwrite these and whatever other mods on 
top of them and THEN change your graphics settings 
to a higher value with CONFIGURATOR at
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/814.

\"WHO SAYZ LOW REZ SUX??\"

All custom and redone from UHD original textures and individually converted to 512k and re-edited. Well... as low res as possible for all items without losing too much.

ESP for Snowless college outside. To bring back snow on outside tiles delete the AAASnowlessCollege.esp.

ESP that adds really awesome music to the college. To remove just delete Magicollege.esp. The floor tiles are from this authors awesome work but I lost the Nexus IP. He deserves all credit for the music and the tile textures.

My FPS has gone from an average world 8 fps to 20 and up using my edited packs but they\'re going to take forever to upload at below 56k so use the TESV pack above and overwrite with mine as they come out.

I take no credits for original works. I\'ve just re-done them for FPS boosts and for use on low end machines. 

No extra crap goes into the skyrim folder with my mods.

This is another of a batch of redone RnE packs by me. I take no credit for the original textures. All I\'ve done is lower the resolution for really old systems to play at higher rez and FPS boosts.

RnE Farmhouses- http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/40075

Also includes meshes\\architecture\\winterhold\\winterholdtrapdoor.nif

Replaced both floor tiles
Edited both windows slightly
